    "summary": "Analyzed the 'mastra' TypeScript Node package inside the brim-PA-backend repo. The graph shows core configuration files (store.config.ts, vector.config.ts) providing Postgres and PgVector-backed stores, a central MCP client (browser-use.client.ts) consumed by multiple agents (flight, hotel, shopping, supervisor), and an index.ts that composes a Mastra instance with storage, vector store and the supervisor agent. Notable patterns: (1) a centralized browser-use MCP client reused by all agents (single point of integration for browser automation); (2) supervisor.agent wires persistent storage, vector store and an embedder (fastembed) for advanced memory; (3) example and package metadata (package.json, docker-compose.yaml) show runtime dependencies and a Postgres/pgvector dev environment. No circular imports were detected in the discovered subset; key hotspots for runtime coupling are the MCP client and the supervisor agent's memory/store configuration."
